00:50:12.000 --> 00:50:19.000
You've already mentioned on the show how Posit has an ambition to build a company, a suite of tools that could last 100 years.

00:50:19.000 --> 00:50:28.000
What kinds of principles or philosophies do you think are critical to creating a legacy that lasts that long in technology?

00:50:28.000 --> 00:50:31.000
Yeah, that's a good question.

00:50:31.000 --> 00:50:34.000
I don't think we know for sure.

00:50:34.000 --> 00:50:44.000
But one of the things that make us different as a company is that we are a public benefit corp, a PBC or a B corp, rather than being an LLC.

00:50:44.000 --> 00:50:57.000
And what that means is kind of fundamentally baked into our charter is that our sole goal is not to optimize shareholder revenue, which is kind of the classic LLC model.

00:50:58.000 --> 00:51:08.000
We explicitly kind of consider other stakeholders like the community and our employees as what we're trying to do as a company.

00:51:08.000 --> 00:51:18.000
And I think that is pretty special because we can say legitimately we don't want to make products that lock you in.

00:51:18.000 --> 00:51:25.000
We want to make products that like, you know, we want to help you and we're going to sell you products that are going to help you do your job.

00:51:25.000 --> 00:51:29.000
And you're going to hopefully pay us money for those because they save you time.

00:51:29.000 --> 00:51:32.000
They allow you to do things that you couldn't otherwise do.

00:51:32.000 --> 00:51:34.000
But we're not just about that money.

00:51:34.000 --> 00:51:38.000
Like we really care about your kind of life as a data scientist.

00:51:38.000 --> 00:51:40.000
We want to build tools for you.

00:51:40.000 --> 00:51:44.000
We want to build tools, open source tools for people that don't have a bunch of money.

00:51:44.000 --> 00:51:46.000
We want to improve academia.

00:51:46.000 --> 00:51:52.000
So I think that that's part of the mission is like we're not just we're not optimizing for short term profit.

00:51:52.000 --> 00:51:55.000
We can say like we're going to take a longer view.

00:51:55.000 --> 00:52:01.000
And, you know, part of that is also like we're not we're not a VC driven company.

00:52:01.000 --> 00:52:05.000
