They're still angry and annoyed by that whole thing,

01:18:22.000 --> 01:18:26.000
and there's kind of no obvious successor in sight.

01:18:26.000 --> 01:18:29.000
You know, I'm on, like, FosterDawn, which, I don't know,

01:18:29.000 --> 01:18:32.000
is only going to appeal to the most technical of technical people.

01:18:32.000 --> 01:18:35.000
I found it hard enough to get up and going on it.

01:18:35.000 --> 01:18:42.000
I'm on LinkedIn, which I still cringe whenever I use LinkedIn.

01:18:42.000 --> 01:18:44.000
But it's fine.

01:18:44.000 --> 01:18:51.000
And then, like, I don't know, Threads just feels like switching one billionaire

01:18:51.000 --> 01:18:52.000
to another billionaire.

01:18:52.000 --> 01:18:54.000
So I've heard good things about Blue Sky,

01:18:54.000 --> 01:18:57.000
and I know people have been encouraging me to check it out,

01:18:57.000 --> 01:18:59.000
so maybe that would be something to try.

01:18:59.000 --> 01:19:03.000
But it's just, like, another social media platform.

01:19:03.000 --> 01:19:08.000
Yeah, that seems to be the way to probably go as a replacement for Twitter.

01:19:08.000 --> 01:19:10.000
It seems to have some momentum.

01:19:10.000 --> 01:19:14.000
