01:19:25.000 --> 01:19:28.000
This is an interesting technical one from Lelouch.

01:19:28.000 --> 01:19:33.000
So does Posit still have plans of developing an online collaborative editing platform

01:19:33.000 --> 01:19:38.000
for Quarto similar to the role that Overleaf has in the LaTeX ecosystem?

01:19:38.000 --> 01:19:39.000
Yes.

01:19:39.000 --> 01:19:40.000
I'd say we definitely have plans.

01:19:40.000 --> 01:19:44.000
Like, this is part of the vision for, like, we want data scientists to be able

01:19:44.000 --> 01:19:48.000
to use Quarto, you know, to communicate with decision makers,

01:19:48.000 --> 01:19:54.000
non-technical folks so they can comment, they can change the writing.

01:19:54.000 --> 01:19:58.000
You know, I think that's still some distance away on our plan,

01:19:58.000 --> 01:20:01.000
but, like, absolutely we really want to make that.

01:20:01.000 --> 01:20:05.000
We really want to make Quarto facilitate the communication between technical

01:20:05.000 --> 01:20:07.000
and non-technical folks as well.

01:20:07.000 --> 01:20:09.000
Nice.

