01:23:39.000 --> 01:23:40.000
In today's episode, Hadley filled us in

01:23:40.000 --> 01:23:42.000
on how the goal of the Tidyverse developers

01:23:42.000 --> 01:23:46.000
is to allow data scientists to spend as much time as possible

01:23:46.000 --> 01:23:48.000
in a flow state.

01:23:48.000 --> 01:23:50.000
He also let us know how two of his favorite R packages

01:23:50.000 --> 01:23:53.000
are dbplyr for converting R to SQL,

01:23:53.000 --> 01:23:56.000
and testbat for unit testing.

01:23:56.000 --> 01:23:59.000
He also talked about how plot9 allows for ggplot2-style

01:24:00.000 --> 01:24:05.000
and sayuba allows for dplyr-like data analysis in Python,

01:24:05.000 --> 01:24:08.000
while arrow, ductdb, and keras for R

01:24:08.000 --> 01:24:11.000
allow R and Python to be more closely married than ever.

01:24:11.000 --> 01:24:14.000
He also talked about how quarto allows natural language and code

01:24:14.000 --> 01:24:18.000
to be easily blended together into beautiful documents.

